      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Strict enforcement protects the domestic labor market by reducing the supply of unauthorized, low-wage labor. When undocumented workers are deterred or removed, employers are incentivized to offer higher wages and better working conditions to legally employed citizens. This competition for workers drives up the baseline wage floor, benefiting the entire low-skilled workforce. Ultimately, controlled immigration ensures that economic benefits accrue to legal residents and citizens.",
      "source": "target",
