      "content": "That's helpful, thanks. One thing my students are worried about is the rebuttal from the other side saying these arguments are just \"fear-mongering\" or economically unsound. To make sure they aren't caught off guard, could you show them how to respond to the claim that increased enforcement actually hurts the economy by creating labor shortages? I want them to be able to defend the idea that enforcement is a net positive for the economy without sounding like they're just ignoring the counterarguments.",
