      "content": "The counterargument about labor shortages is a false dichotomy that ignores the structural issues in the labor market. While some sectors may face temporary adjustments, the long-term economic stability provided by a secure, rule-abiding workforce outweighs these transient concerns. Moreover, strict enforcement encourages formalization, which increases tax revenue and compliance, providing a more sustainable economic foundation than an informal, unregulated labor market. The economic costs of unchecked migration far surpass the costs of effective border management.",
